        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 2:28AM CDT by NWS Corpus Christi TX</headline>
        <description>At 227 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Skidmore, moving northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Skidmore and Tynan.

This includes US Highway 181 between mile markers 598 and 610.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
